result.execSummary:
The defendant Kirah S. Nolan was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endanger Safety/Use/Dangerous Weapon [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(a).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
Costs waived by the Court.

The Defendant is to undergo any counseling the agent finds appropriate and must comply with any recommended treatment/assessment/counseling.  The Defendant is to complete the Domestic Violence Intervention Program.  The Defendant is to obtain and maintain full time employment and/or educational programming as recommended.  The Defendant is to obtain a GED/HSED or equivalent.  The no contact with the victim is left up to the Agent.  The Defendant is not to possess any weapons.  Court orders expungement per Wisconsin Statute #973.015, upon successful completion of probation (no holds, ATRs or revocations) and completing an additional 20 hours of community service per Count.  Expungement is granted on 3 Counts only between the two files (15CM165 & 14CM634).  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due, and/or other collection means, such as income assignment will be issued.
